# We don't want trash from the console – it just pollutes the project.
# These are logs: the digital equivalent of farting in an elevator.
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
lerna-debug.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# Node.js sometimes creates a 'report' if things crash.
# Think of it as a crime scene photo. We don't want to share that.
report.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.[0-9]*.json

# These files track running processes.
# But once the app stops, they become useless zombies. Ignore them.
pids
*.pid
*.seed
*.pid.lock

# These are created when tools like jscoverage test our code.
# It’s like putting a microscope on your code, but we don’t commit the microscope results.
lib-cov

# Coverage reports from test tools (like Istanbul).
# Think of it as exam papers—important to see once, but not submit to Git.
coverage
*.lcov

# nyc also creates test coverage data.
# It’s like your coaching class’s notes—private.
.nyc_output

# Grunt is a task runner. This folder stores temporary mess while it works.
# Like a carpenter’s dust during furniture work. No need to store it.
.grunt

# Bower is an old package manager.
# These are its downloaded packages. No need to upload what's already free.
bower_components

# If node-waf configures something, it drops this file.
# Not needed in our version control.
.lock-wscript

# Compiled binary files live here. Heavy, machine-specific stuff.
# You don’t post your blood reports in a resume—same logic.
build/Release

# These folders contain libraries downloaded by package managers.
# Never upload these—they’re like ingredients you can always re-buy.
node_modules/
jspm_packages/

# Snowpack, another tool, stores downloaded dependencies here.
web_modules/

# TypeScript remembers what it compiled last time in these files.
# Like your brain caching yesterday’s homework. Not needed in Git.
*.tsbuildinfo

# npm stores its downloaded cache here.
# Think of it as a grocery bag after emptying it. Bin it.
.npm

# eslint helps fix your code’s grammar.
# It stores corrections in a cache—private stuff. Not for the repo.
.eslintcache

# stylelint does for CSS what eslint does for JS.
# Again, its cache is like scratch paper. Don’t commit.
.stylelintcache

# Microbundle cache folders. Store pre-built bundles.
# Like a chef’s pre-prepped food—nice, but temporary.
.rpt2_cache/
.rts2_cache_cjs/
.rts2_cache_es/
.rts2_cache_umd/

# History from Node.js terminal (REPL).
# Like your doodles during a lecture. Not worth sharing.
.node_repl_history

# This is created if you bundle your package using `npm pack`.
# It’s like gift-wrapping your code. We don’t version the wrapping.
*.tgz

# Integrity check file for yarn.
# Like a stamp of trust between you and yarn. No need to share.
.yarn-integrity

# These are your environment secrets (passwords, tokens).
# Like your ATM PIN. Never ever post this online!
.env
.env.development.local
.env.test.local
.env.production.local
.env.local

# Parcel (a bundler) saves temporary files here.
# Like scribbles while making an artwork. Skip them.
.cache
.parcel-cache

# Next.js puts its build output in `.next` and `out/`
# Final artwork. Let Git ignore it because it’s auto-generated.
.next
out

# Nuxt.js is similar to Next.js. It builds into this folder.
.nuxt
dist

# Gatsby builds and caches data here.
.cache/

# If you use Gatsby, public/ may be important. Uncomment the next line if needed.
# public

# VuePress creates output here.
.vuepress/dist

# VuePress v2 uses .temp to store stuff temporarily.
.temp

# Docusaurus—another documentation tool—creates this folder.
.docusaurus

# Serverless framework builds stuff here.
.serverless/

# FuseBox cache. Tool-specific again. No need in Git.
.fusebox/

# Local DB files for testing DynamoDB.
.dynamodb/

# TernJS writes a port file here.
# Like a shortcut key config. Ignore it.
.tern-port

# VSCode extension testers use this to track different versions.
.vscode-test

# Yarn v2 creates these cache and state files.
# Think of it as yarn’s diary. Keep it private.
.yarn/cache
.yarn/unplugged
.yarn/build-state.yml
.yarn/install-state.gz
.pnp.*

# Serverless + Webpack output. Again, temporary constructions.
.webpack/

# SvelteKit builds here. Auto-generated = skip.
.svelte-kit
